                       "message":  "fix(editor): GlbWatcher accepts bare relative paths via cwd\n\nGlbWatcher::new resolved the directory to watch via\nglb_source_path.parent().ok_or_else(...). That path treats Some(\"\")\nidentically to a valid parent, but Path::parent() returns Some(\"\") --\nnot None -- for bare relative filenames like `asset.glb`. The empty\npath then propagated into watcher.watch(\"\") which fails on every\nplatform; the binary only warn-logs construction errors, so launching\nthe editor with `--glb asset.glb` from the asset directory silently\ndisabled automatic reload (manual R-key still worked, masking the bug\nduring smoke testing).\n\nExtract `watch_parent_for` as a pure helper that normalizes Some(\"\")\nto \".\" while still erroring on a truly empty input path. The watcher\nconstructor calls it. Module-level + constructor doc-comments now\nstate the resolution rule and table the resolution matrix so a future\nmaintainer sees the intent before re-introducing the bug.\n\nTests:\n  - watch_parent_for_bare_relative_resolves_to_dot\n  - watch_parent_for_dot_slash_relative_resolves_to_dot\n  - watch_parent_for_nested_relative_resolves_to_parent_dir\n  - watch_parent_for_empty_path_errors\n  - new_accepts_bare_relative_path_by_watching_cwd (end-to-end smoke\n    constructing a real platform watcher against the cwd)\n\nSalvages ai-dispatch/ISSUE-85 -- this was one of the two Codex control\nblockers; the other (Cargo.lock dependency-edge change for `notify` in\nrge-editor) is being approved by the human reviewer as scope-creep on\nthe original task.",
